FBIS4-39284 "drsov109_a_94008" FBIS-SOV-94-109 Daily Report 4 Jun 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Further Reportage on ROK President's Visit Further Reportage on ROK President's Visit Meets ITAR-TASS General Director LD0406134194 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1326 GMT 4 Jun 94 LD0406134194 Moscow ITAR-TASS English BFN [By ITAR-TASS correspondent] [Text] Moscow June 4 TASS -- South Korean President Kim Young- sam has received ITAR-TASS General Director Vitaliy Ignatenko for an unofficial meeting to discuss aspects of and prospects for Russian- South Korean interaction in information, publishing and humanitarian spheres. When heading the NOVOYE VREMYA journal, Vitaliy Ignatenko was a first Russian correspondent to keep contact with South Korean opposition leader Kim Young-sam and used the journal to call for the establishment of Russian-South Korean diplomatic relations. ITAR-TASS sent its correspondent to Seoul before the official Russian recognition of South Korea, and he is still the only Russian newsman in South Korea, a most dynamically developing state of the Asia-Pacific region.
